# AWS Multi-AZ Highly Available Web Application

## 📌 Project Objective

Deploy a fault-tolerant and highly available web application across multiple Availability Zones using AWS core services.

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

This project uses:

* Custom VPC (10.0.0.0/16)
* 2 Public Subnets (Multi-AZ)
* 2 Private Subnets (Multi-AZ)
* Internet Gateway & NAT Gateway
* EC2 Instances (Private Subnets)
* Application Load Balancer (Public Subnets)
* Auto Scaling Group (Min:2, Desired:2)
* S3 Bucket for static assets
* CloudWatch Alarm (CPU > 70%)

## ⚙️ Services Used

* Amazon Web Services
* Amazon EC2
* Amazon VPC
* Elastic Load Balancing
* Amazon S3
* Amazon CloudWatch
* AWS Auto Scaling

## 🚀 Deployment Steps

1. Created custom VPC and subnets across multiple AZs.
2. Configured Internet Gateway and NAT Gateway.
3. Launched EC2 instances in private subnets.
4. Configured ALB in public subnets.
5. Attached EC2 instances to Target Group.
6. Configured Auto Scaling Group.
7. Uploaded static content to S3.
8. Created CloudWatch Alarm for CPU utilization > 70%.
9. Tested application using ALB DNS URL.

## 📊 Result

The application remains available even if one Availability Zone fails. Auto Scaling ensures performance under high load.

